# Operator-private content (automations, sensor/template lists, custom
# blueprints) is excluded from git so personal automation logic doesn't
# land in the repo. Placeholder stubs at these paths ARE committed (force-
# added past these patterns) so the role's `copy:` task converges on a
# fresh clone and in CI; the operator's local working-tree content shadows
# them and `git update-index --skip-worktree <path>` in the operator's
# main worktree keeps the divergence out of `git status`.
automations.yaml
macros.jinja
sensors.yaml
templates.yaml
covers.yaml
blueprints/
